notesStmt.note: 1 older paper flyleaf at the beginning of the manuscript with birth notes, 16th century (folio 1r).
Inscription in an initial-word panel: 'Yishmael, Nehemiah, Raphael, Hayim Ottolenghi, Judah Eliezer, Nahman, brothers, sons of Menahem' (folio 110v).
Italian inscription: belonged to the Foa Library in Reggio ([iv verso], inside front cover).
Manuscript description based on Margoliouth, G.: Catalogue of the Hebrew and Samaritan Manuscripts in the British Museum, London 1965.

layoutDesc.layout: Columns: 1; ruled lines: 26; written lines: 25; Uniform layout. Visible complete hard-point ruling. Hair side and flesh side of folios distinguishable. All books except Joel, Amos, Obadiah, Jonah and Nahum begin a new page. Judges, Samuel, Isaiah, Jeremiah, Hosea and Micah commence a new leaf. Hafṭarot are indicated in the margins by a later hand. Another hand has numbered the chapters with Hebrew letters and added the titles in the upper margin.

scriptDesc.scriptNote: Ashkenazi square script (punctuated), Italian semi-cursive script (unpunctuated) of the 14th to 15th century. Meshulam: written in red in the text, folio 166r.

binding.p: BM in-house. Spine: 'Former & Latter Prophets. Hebrew. Brit. Mus. Additional Ms. 11657.'

history.provenance: Acquisition: Thomas Rodd the younger (b. 1796, d. 1849): purchased from him by the British Museum on 21 September 1839 : inscribed, [334v]).
